I leave it to you.

21:00.131 --> 21:01.131
Good-bye, Maile.

21:01.132 --> 21:02.633
Good-bye, Mr. Gates.

21:20.151 --> 21:21.151
Hi, O'Hara.

21:21.152 --> 21:22.152
Hi.

21:22.153 --> 21:23.654
Don't you dig judo?

21:23.655 --> 21:25.656
Man don't live
on muscles alone.

21:25.657 --> 21:27.658
You got any ketchup
in that bag?

21:27.659 --> 21:29.159
No, but I have
some lipstick.

21:29.160 --> 21:30.160
Same color.

21:30.161 --> 21:31.662
Nah. Lipstick,
like, fattening.

21:31.663 --> 21:33.664
<i>I'm</i> on a diet.

21:33.665 --> 21:35.165
Oh, yeah.

21:35.166 --> 21:36.667
Where's Chad?

21:36.668 --> 21:38.168
Back in the briny.

21:38.169 --> 21:40.120
It's just like
he never left.

21:40.121 --> 21:41.672
Even though
there's no surf,

21:41.673 --> 21:43.173
he's right back
in the swim.

21:43.174 --> 21:45.676
Well, he's about
to be beached.

22:09.200 --> 22:12.202
Well, it's about time
you got here.

22:12.203 --> 22:14.705
I sneaked away half an hour
early as it is.

22:14.706 --> 22:16.707
The fellas are playing
for a luau tonight at the outrigger.

22:16.708 --> 22:18.208
I told them
to count us in.

22:18.209 --> 22:20.711
Can't. The whole family's
meeting in Haleiwa tonight.

22:20.712 --> 22:22.212
At your grandmother's?

22:22.213 --> 22:24.214
It's her birthday.
She's 78.

22:24.215 --> 22:25.716
Well, that's something
to celebrate.

22:25.717 --> 22:27.217
Am I invited?

22:27.218 --> 22:28.719
You're hiding out,
remember?

22:28.720 --> 22:30.220
Not from <i>your</i> folks.

22:30.221 --> 22:31.221
Yours, either.

22:31.222 --> 22:32.222
Huh?

22:32.223 --> 22:34.725
Your father came
to see me today.

22:35.727 --> 22:38.729
He knows you're back.

22:38.730 --> 22:41.181
You've got to go
home sometime. Why?

22:41.182 --> 22:43.734
You can't spend
the rest of your life on a surfboard.

22:43.735 --> 22:45.235
Oh, yes, I can.

22:45.236 --> 22:47.237
The G.I. bill
of rights

22:47.238 --> 22:49.239
says I get
my old job back.

22:49.240 --> 22:50.741
This is my old job.

22:50.742 --> 22:54.244
Like I said,
yankee, go home!

22:54.245 --> 22:55.746
Hey, wait a...

22:55.747 --> 22:57.247
Hey, wait!

22:57.248 --> 22:59.250
I'll get you!

23:00.251 --> 23:02.753
It's certainly nice
to have you here.

23:02.754 --> 23:03.754
Thank you, Fred.

23:03.755 --> 23:05.255
Oh, here we are.

23:05.256 --> 23:08.258
Daddy, let's drink
a toast to your boss.

23:08.259 --> 23:09.259
Aloha, Jack.

23:09.260 --> 23:10.260
Aloha.

23:10.261 --> 23:11.261
Aloha, daddy.

23:11.262 --> 23:12.263
Aloha.

23:13.765 --> 23:16.266
You know,
every time I come here,

23:16.267 --> 23:17.768
I feel like
a prize fool.

23:17.769 --> 23:19.770
I've seen the latest
company statement

23:19.771 --> 23:21.271
raising
the dividends.

23:21.272 --> 23:22.272
You're no fool,
boss.

23:22.273 --> 23:24.775
Oh, no? Then how come
I moved you here

23:24.776 --> 23:26.777
and kept myself
on the mainland?

23:26.778 --> 23:28.779
To your glorious
Hawaiian winters.

23:28.780 --> 23:29.780
Aloha, Jack.

23:29.781 --> 23:31.281
Aloha.

23:31.282 --> 23:32.283
Aloha.

23:40.792 --> 23:42.793
Missa Gates! Missa Gates!

23:42.794 --> 23:44.795
Missa Gates! Missa Gates!
Missa Gates!

23:44.796 --> 23:46.747
Missa Gates,
guess who here!

23:46.748 --> 23:47.798
He's home!

23:47.799 --> 23:49.299
Just drive up in car,
all the way from Army!

23:49.300 --> 23:50.300
Who?

23:50.301 --> 23:51.802
Our boy Chadwick!

23:51.803 --> 23:52.803
Chadwick!

23:52.804 --> 23:54.805
Oh, daddy, Jack,
it's Chadwick!

23:54.806 --> 23:56.807
My boy's home
from the war!

23:56.808 --> 23:58.809
Sarah Lee, there
wasn't any war.

23:59.811 --> 24:01.311
Well, don't just
stand there!

24:01.312 --> 24:02.312
Aloha.

24:02.313 --> 24:04.314
Chadwick?

24:04.315 --> 24:05.816
Oh, Chadwick, my boy!

24:05.817 --> 24:06.817
Hiya, Mom!

24:06.818 --> 24:08.318
Welcome home, son.

24:08.319 --> 24:09.319
Hi, Pop. Hey, Jack!

24:09.320 --> 24:10.821
Didn't expect
to see you here.

24:10.822 --> 24:11.822
Arrived yesterday.

24:11.823 --> 24:12.823
Just checking up
on your old man.

24:12.824 --> 24:13.824
You're looking
good, fella.

24:13.825 --> 24:14.825
Thank you.

24:14.826 --> 24:16.326
Ping Pong, will you
shut off that water?

24:16.327 --> 24:17.828
Don't get wet.

24:20.331 --> 24:21.832
Hello, Mr. Chadwick.

24:21.833 --> 24:23.834
You have swinging
time in Europe?

24:23.835 --> 24:26.336
Pingo,
the swingingest, boy.

24:26.337 --> 24:27.337
How are you,
boy?

24:27.338 --> 24:28.339
Hi, Jack. Hi, Pop.

24:28.840 --> 24:30.280
Doesn't he look
marvelous in uniform?

24:30.341 --> 24:31.341
Go get the camera,
daddy.

24:31.342 --> 24:32.843
Later, Sarah Lee.
Later.

24:32.844 --> 24:34.845
Come on in. We got
so much to talk about.

24:34.846 --> 24:36.847
I have to get my bags, Mom.

24:36.848 --> 24:38.849
Don't worry, Mr. Chadwick.
I get bags...

24:41.352 --> 24:42.853
Aloha!

24:45.356 --> 24:47.357
I got it!
I got it!

24:47.358 --> 24:48.859
Ping Pong,

24:48.860 --> 24:51.361
tell cook we'll let her know
when to start serving.

24:51.362 --> 24:52.863
We want to talk
to our boy.

24:52.864 --> 24:54.364
<i>Oui, oui,</i>
missy.

24:54.365 --> 24:57.367
We must give
a welcome-home party for Chadwick, daddy,

24:57.368 --> 24:58.869
and it could be
for Jack, too.

24:58.870 --> 25:00.370
Oh, forget about
me, Sarah Lee.

25:00.371 --> 25:01.872
Just invite
Chad's friends.

25:01.873 --> 25:04.374
You mean those nasty
little beach boys?

25:04.375 --> 25:05.876
Oh, no. Now that
Chadwick's home,

25:05.877 --> 25:07.878
I'm sure he's got
all that foolishness

25:07.879 --> 25:10.380
out of his system...
After the war.

25:10.381 --> 25:11.381
Sarah Lee,

25:11.382 --> 25:13.383
how many times do
I have to tell you,

25:13.384 --> 25:14.885
he was not in a war.

25:14.886 --> 25:16.386
Oh, I know
you're right, daddy,

25:16.387 --> 25:18.889
but if I don't tell
myself there was a war,

25:18.890 --> 25:20.891
I have a most
depressing feeling

25:20.892 --> 25:22.893
Chadwick's
just wasted 2 years.

25:22.894 --> 25:25.897
Chadwick, sweet boy.

25:26.898 --> 25:28.899
Sure feels good to get
back into civvies, Mom.

25:28.900 --> 25:30.901
Oh, why'd you take off
your soldier suit?

25:30.902 --> 25:32.402
You looked
so handsome in it,

25:32.403 --> 25:33.904
just like
Stonewall Jackson.

25:33.905 --> 25:36.406
Hey, you got some sugar
for your mama?

25:36.407 --> 25:38.408
How about a drink
before dinner, civilian?

25:38.409 --> 25:39.910
Why don't you give him

25:39.911 --> 25:41.411
some of your
pineapple juice, Jack?

25:41.412 --> 25:42.913
Missed it, huh, boy?

25:42.914 --> 25:43.914
Yeah.

25:43.915 --> 25:45.916
You should try
the new rum drink.

25:45.917 --> 25:46.917
Jack...

25:46.918 --> 25:48.919
Chadwick's
a growing boy, Fred,

25:48.920 --> 25:51.421
and I don't think it
proper for his daddy

25:51.422 --> 25:52.923
to give him
intoxicating libations.

25:52.924 --> 25:54.875
Mom, I'd like to
tell you about the...

25:54.876 --> 25:56.927
We were just talking
about your party, son.

25:56.928 --> 25:59.429
What party?
Your coming-home party

25:59.430 --> 26:01.932
to celebrate your return
from the war.

26:01.933 --> 26:04.434
We can have the Wilsons
and the pomfrets.

26:04.435 --> 26:05.436
Oh, yes,
they're a must.

26:05.937 --> 26:08.939
They get absolutely
hilarious at parties.

26:08.940 --> 26:11.942
They get
absolutely stoned, is what they get.

26:11.943 --> 26:12.943
Yes.

26:12.944 --> 26:13.945
Uh, Chadwick,

26:14.445 --> 26:15.946
I think it would be
much impressier

26:15.947 --> 26:18.949
if you wore your uniform
with all the medals you won.

26:18.950 --> 26:20.951
I didn't win
any medals, Mom.

26:20.952 --> 26:22.452
Of course
you won medals.

26:22.453 --> 26:23.954
What were all those
on your soldier suit?

26:23.955 --> 26:25.455
Just marksmanship
and good conduct.

26:25.456 --> 26:26.957
Oh, you see, daddy?

26:26.958 --> 26:28.458
Every soldier wins one

26:28.459 --> 26:30.460
if he hits the target
instead of an officer.

26:30.461 --> 26:31.962
Oh, you put me in mind

26:31.963 --> 26:33.463
of my great-grandfather
on my side,

26:33.464 --> 26:34.965
Captain Matthew Polk.

26:34.966 --> 26:36.974
Oh, he was one
o <i>the</i> bravest men

26:36.975 --> 26:38.976
in the war
between the states.

26:38.977 --> 26:40.978
Oh, the daring deeds
that man performed,

26:40.979 --> 26:42.479
his bravery under fire,

26:42.480 --> 26:44.982
his courage
on the field of battle

26:44.983 --> 26:47.484
made us all proud
to be Polks.

26:47.485 --> 26:49.486
Oh, it's such a shame

26:49.487 --> 26:51.989
Captain Polk
was a damn yankee.

26:51.990 --> 26:54.492
Chad, which one
do you want?

26:56.494 --> 26:58.495
Well, let me see.

26:58.496 --> 27:00.498
You need it, boy.
Take your pick.

27:02.000 --> 27:03.500
Whew.
I think I'll stick

27:03.501 --> 27:05.002
to the straight
pineapple juice.

27:05.003 --> 27:07.505
We must decide
on the orchestra for the party.

27:08.006 --> 27:09.246
Oh, well,
if you'll excuse me,

27:09.507 --> 27:11.387
I think I'll freshen up
a little before dinner.

27:11.509 --> 27:12.009
Aloha.

27:12.510 --> 27:13.510
Yeah.

27:13.511 --> 27:15.191
Orchestra? Say, Mom,
how about my friends?

27:15.513 --> 27:16.593
You mean those
native boys?

27:17.015 --> 27:18.455
The swingingest group
in the islands.

27:18.516 --> 27:20.017
Oh, they are not
musicians, Chadwick.

27:20.518 --> 27:21.519
They're just
beach boys.

27:22.020 --> 27:23.340
Mom, they've turned
professional.

27:23.521 --> 27:24.881
They do a lot of work
around town.

27:25.023 --> 27:26.024
How'd you know that?

27:26.524 --> 27:27.525
Uh, why...

27:28.026 --> 27:29.027
he corresponded
with them

27:29.527 --> 27:31.028
while he was
in Europe.

27:31.529 --> 27:33.030
Now, Chadwick,
we might as well

27:33.531 --> 27:35.032
have an understanding
right off.

27:35.533 --> 27:37.034
You've come home
to stay,

27:37.535 --> 27:39.537
and your life's
going to be different.

27:40.038 --> 27:41.398
You're going
to associate yourself

27:41.539 --> 27:43.540
with the finer elements
on this island,

27:43.541 --> 27:46.043
and you're going to have
a responsible position

27:46.044 --> 27:48.045
with the Great Southern
Hawaiian Fruit Company,

27:48.046 --> 27:51.048
and you're going to marry
a girl of your own class

27:51.049 --> 27:53.051
and be a gentleman
like your daddy.

27:54.052 --> 27:56.054
Mom, do we have to
discuss this now?

27:56.554 --> 27:59.056
Yes. I don't want you
wasting your precious time

27:59.557 --> 28:01.558
on those beach boys
or that native girl.

28:01.559 --> 28:04.561
Sarah Lee,
the boy just came home.

28:04.562 --> 28:05.904
I think
he should know

28:05.905 --> 28:07.906
exactly what
we expect of him.

28:07.907 --> 28:09.407
I know what
you expect of me.

28:09.408 --> 28:11.409
I thought maybe after
a hitch in the army,

28:11.410 --> 28:13.411
I could come back and
do what you want me to,

28:13.412 --> 28:14.913
but now I know I can't.

28:14.914 --> 28:16.915
Well, how do you know?
You just got back.

28:16.916 --> 28:18.917
I've been back
for 5 days, Mom.

28:18.918 --> 28:19.918
5 days?

28:19.919 --> 28:21.920
Yes, and for 5 days,
I've been at the beach,

28:21.921 --> 28:23.421
living in my shack
and dreading the time

28:23.422 --> 28:25.423
I would have to come
back here and tell you

28:25.424 --> 28:26.925
I'm not going to
go to work

28:26.926 --> 28:28.927
for the Great Southern
Hawaiian Fruit Company.

28:28.928 --> 28:29.928
Sarah Lee.

28:29.929 --> 28:31.429
Yes, daddy?

28:31.430 --> 28:33.431
Let's talk about it
tomorrow, son.

28:33.432 --> 28:34.432
Home 5 days,

28:34.433 --> 28:36.434
and he didn't even
come to his mother.

28:36.435 --> 28:38.436
Mom, it's time
I started

28:38.437 --> 28:39.938
doing something
for myself,

28:39.939 --> 28:41.440
like making my
own decisions.

28:42.942 --> 28:45.410
Chadwick!

28:45.411 --> 28:46.444
Chadwick!

28:46.445 --> 28:47.946
Your mother
hasn't finished,

28:47.947 --> 28:49.948
and you haven't
had your dinner.

28:49.949 --> 28:51.449
All of a sudden,
I'm not hungry.

28:51.450 --> 28:52.451
Good night.

28:56.956 --> 28:58.957
And he didn't even
give his mama

28:58.958 --> 28:59.959
any good-night sugar.

29:00.459 --> 29:01.960
Sarah Lee,
there are times

29:02.461 --> 29:04.463
when I could wring
your fool neck.

29:21.981 --> 29:24.483
Good evening, sir.
I'll take care of your car.

29:24.984 --> 29:25.984
Thank you.

30:13.499 --> 30:14.532
Grandma!

30:14.533 --> 30:16.534
No! No, no.

30:16.535 --> 30:19.037
No, no, no!

30:37.556 --> 30:39.557
Well, it is a pleasant
surprise, Chad.

30:39.558 --> 30:41.059
Thanks, Mr. Duval.

30:41.060 --> 30:42.560
We were not
expecting you.

30:42.561 --> 30:45.563
I just came by
to pay my respects to Maile's grandmother.

30:45.564 --> 30:47.065
Maile!

30:49.068 --> 30:50.568
We have a visitor.

30:50.569 --> 30:52.070
He says he dropped by

30:52.071 --> 30:54.573
to pay his respects
to your grandmother.

30:55.074 --> 30:56.075
Excuse me.

30:56.575 --> 30:58.076
I thought
you were going home.

30:58.577 --> 31:00.578
I did. I'm out
on good behavior.

31:00.579 --> 31:02.080
Mmm.

31:02.081 --> 31:04.083
Your father said he
was glad to see me.

31:04.583 --> 31:06.585
Well, I'm glad
to see you, too.

31:08.087 --> 31:10.088
Come wish grandmother
a happy birthday.

31:10.089 --> 31:13.092
Grandmother,
you remember Chad.

31:13.592 --> 31:16.094
I am delighted
to see you again, Chad.

31:16.095 --> 31:17.596
Welcome back
from the army.

31:18.097 --> 31:19.657
Aloha, Mrs. manaka,
and happy birthday.

31:20.099 --> 31:22.100
I brought you
a gift from Austria.

31:22.101 --> 31:23.601
Thank you,

31:23.602 --> 31:26.104
but the light you kindle
in my granddaughter's eye

31:26.105 --> 31:27.606
is gift enough.

31:29.108 --> 31:30.608
It's a music box.

31:30.609 --> 31:32.110
It plays a European
love song,

31:32.111 --> 31:34.112
but they're the same
in any language.

31:39.118 --> 31:45.123
♪ Wise men say ♪

31:45.124 --> 31:47.625
♪ Only fools ♪

31:47.626 --> 31:51.129
♪ Rush in ♪

31:52.631 --> 31:58.136
♪ But I can't help ♪

31:58.137 --> 32:05.144
♪ Falling in love
with you ♪

32:06.645 --> 32:13.151
♪ Shall I stay? ♪

32:13.152 --> 32:20.158
♪ Would it be
a sin? ♪

32:20.159 --> 32:25.664
♪ If I can't help ♪

32:26.081 --> 32:34.172
♪ Falling in love
with you ♪

32:34.173 --> 32:37.675
♪ Like a river
flows ♪

32:37.676 --> 32:41.179
♪ Surely
to the sea ♪

32:41.180 --> 32:44.682
♪ Darling,
so it goes ♪

32:44.683 --> 32:51.189
♪ Some things
are meant to be ♪

32:51.190 --> 32:57.695
♪ Take my hand ♪

32:57.696 --> 33:04.202
♪ Take my whole
life, too ♪

33:05.204 --> 33:10.708
♪ For I can't help ♪

33:10.709 --> 33:14.212
♪ Falling in love ♪

33:14.213 --> 33:18.216
♪ With ♪

33:18.217 --> 33:21.220
♪ You ♪

33:23.722 --> 33:25.223
That's lovely, Chad.

33:25.224 --> 33:27.226
And so are you,
grandmother.

33:45.744 --> 33:47.745
Sure beats lunch
in town, doesn't it?

33:47.746 --> 33:49.247
Mmm.

33:49.248 --> 33:51.249
You don't get this view
in town, either.

33:51.250 --> 33:54.253
No, and it was easier
to get a reservation here.

34:13.772 --> 34:15.773
Your grandmother
packs a pretty picnic.

34:15.774 --> 34:18.275
The way
to a man's heart.

34:18.277 --> 34:20.277
She's making sure
I reach yours,

34:20.279 --> 34:22.280
especially after
last night.

34:22.281 --> 34:24.282
She loved the music box.

34:24.283 --> 34:26.784
I'm glad.
She's a wonderful lady.

34:26.784 --> 34:29.286
The difference between
your family and mine.

34:29.288 --> 34:30.788
We're not
our families, Chad.

34:30.789 --> 34:32.790
We're what we make
of ourselves.

34:32.791 --> 34:33.791
You know, you're right.

34:33.792 --> 34:35.793
And if I'm going to make
anything of myself,

34:35.793 --> 34:37.295
it's about time
to get started

34:37.295 --> 34:38.795
and take hold of things.

34:38.797 --> 34:40.799
While you're in the mood
to take hold...

34:44.303 --> 34:46.804
Maile, I've got
to get a job.

34:46.804 --> 34:48.306
And, I gather,

34:48.306 --> 34:50.308
<i>not</i> in your father's
pineapple plant.

34:50.309 --> 34:51.309
No, ma'am.

34:51.310 --> 34:52.310
No red carpet,

34:52.311 --> 34:53.811
where everybody
knows who I am.

34:53.812 --> 34:55.313
"He's the boss' son.
Be nice to him."

34:55.813 --> 34:56.813
that's not for me.

34:56.815 --> 34:58.316
Hawaii has a big future.

34:58.817 --> 35:00.818
I want to become
a part of it.

35:00.819 --> 35:02.820
I'm young and healthy.
I'm not <i>too</i> stupid.

35:02.821 --> 35:03.821
Well, wonderful.

35:03.822 --> 35:05.823
This place is growing
by leaps and bounds.

35:05.824 --> 35:07.144
There are
more tourists come here

35:07.326 --> 35:08.826
than any other state
in the union.

35:08.827 --> 35:09.827
Hey, that's it!

35:09.828 --> 35:11.829
I'm glad you
thought of it.

35:11.830 --> 35:12.831
What did I think of?

35:13.131 --> 35:13.831
Tourist business...
Your business.

35:14.333 --> 35:15.333
It's booming, isn't it?

35:15.334 --> 35:16.834
It's getting bigger
all the time.

35:16.835 --> 35:18.235
I know every inch
of these islands.

35:18.337 --> 35:19.337
I'd make a good
tourist guide.

35:19.338 --> 35:20.658
You'd make a great
tourist guide.

35:20.839 --> 35:21.839
I'll put a word in
with my boss.

35:21.840 --> 35:23.841
No, you don't.
I'll put in my own word.

35:23.842 --> 35:25.843
This mission is
strictly solo, you hear?

35:25.844 --> 35:27.845
You're coming in
loud and proud.

35:27.846 --> 35:29.847
I got to get going.
I got to see your boss!

35:29.848 --> 35:31.849
I've wasted
too much time already.

35:31.850 --> 35:33.851
Chad!

35:33.852 --> 35:36.354
Haven't you
forgotten something?

35:36.355 --> 35:38.357
Oh. Oh, yeah.

35:48.367 --> 35:50.869
Hey! Hey!

35:53.872 --> 35:55.373
What about me?

35:55.374 --> 35:57.376
Oh. Oh, yeah!

36:19.398 --> 36:21.399
These are not
only decorative,

36:21.400 --> 36:23.401
but they keep
my neck warm.

36:23.402 --> 36:26.404
Now, then, let me see.
Where were we?

36:26.405 --> 36:28.406
Uh, we were somewhere,
weren't we?

36:28.407 --> 36:29.907
Oh, yes. I was
telling you about

36:29.908 --> 36:31.409
my having 2 years
at the university

36:31.910 --> 36:33.070
before I went
to the mainland

36:33.412 --> 36:34.912
and joined the army.

36:34.913 --> 36:36.414
The army? Oh.

36:36.415 --> 36:37.415
Well, that's a lovely
organization.

36:37.416 --> 36:38.916
Yes.

36:38.917 --> 36:41.919
And you say you've
lived here for 50 years?

36:41.920 --> 36:44.422
50... No, 15 years,
ever since my father

36:44.423 --> 36:46.424
was transferred from
the Atlanta office.

36:46.425 --> 36:48.926
That's where Chad was born,
Mr. Chapman.

36:48.927 --> 36:50.428
Huh?

36:50.429 --> 36:51.429
Atlanta.

36:51.430 --> 36:54.432
Oh! Oh, he was.
Yes.

36:54.433 --> 36:56.434
Where is
the crouching lion?

36:56.435 --> 36:57.935
That's a rock formation

36:57.936 --> 36:59.937
on a cliff just north
of kaaawa beach.

36:59.938 --> 37:02.440
It used to be
a native fishing shrine.

37:02.441 --> 37:04.942
Well. Say, that's good.
That's very good.

37:04.943 --> 37:08.446
Yes, that's excellent.
I'm testing you, you see.

37:08.447 --> 37:09.947
Have to be on your toes

37:09.948 --> 37:11.449
if you want to work
for a man like me,

37:11.450 --> 37:12.450
eh, Miss Duval?

37:12.451 --> 37:13.451
Yes, sir.

37:13.452 --> 37:15.453
Yes, you do.

37:15.454 --> 37:18.956
Now, then, I am a tourist
from Chillicothe, Ohio,

37:18.957 --> 37:21.459
and I want to see some
night-blooming cereus blossoms.

37:21.460 --> 37:22.960
Where would you
take me?

37:22.961 --> 37:25.463
I would take you
to the Punahou School.

37:25.464 --> 37:27.965
The Punahou... you would?
That is good.

37:27.966 --> 37:30.468
Yes, well...
That's splendid.

37:30.469 --> 37:32.970
This young man knows,
Miss Duval.

37:32.971 --> 37:35.973
I think he might do.
He might.

37:35.974 --> 37:37.975
Well, I'll think it over.

37:37.976 --> 37:39.977
When will you
let me know, sir?

37:39.978 --> 37:41.979
Well, when <i>I</i> know,
of course.

37:41.980 --> 37:43.981
Oh. Yes, sir.

37:43.982 --> 37:45.983
Thank you,
Mr. Chapman.

37:45.984 --> 37:47.986
Thank you,
Mr. Chapman.

37:53.492 --> 37:54.992
Beautiful.

37:54.993 --> 37:56.494
Beautiful!

37:56.495 --> 37:58.497
That's Mr. Chadwick.

37:58.997 --> 38:00.998
Quick, cover it up,
Ping Pong.

38:00.999 --> 38:03.000
I don't want him
to see it.

38:03.001 --> 38:05.002
Oh, everything
looks so festive,

38:05.003 --> 38:06.504
doesn't it, daddy?

38:06.505 --> 38:07.505
Yes.

38:07.506 --> 38:08.506
Where's Chadwick?

38:08.507 --> 38:09.507
He's on the telephone.

38:09.508 --> 38:10.508
Straighten your tie.

38:10.509 --> 38:12.009
Oh, I do hope
he's dressed.

38:12.010 --> 38:13.511
Is he dressed?

38:13.512 --> 38:15.513
He was the last time
I looked.

38:15.514 --> 38:17.515
Fetch me a mai-tai,
Ping Pong.

38:17.516 --> 38:19.016
Oh, we got enough
bar glasses? I'll check.

38:19.017 --> 38:23.021
Oh, do that.
Oh, parties, parties.

38:24.022 --> 38:25.523
Mr. Chapman didn't
promise anything

38:26.024 --> 38:27.024
when I saw him today.

38:27.025 --> 38:29.026
I know, but something
came up unexpectedly,

38:29.027 --> 38:30.528
and he needs you.

38:30.529 --> 38:33.531
It's a new client...
A schoolteacher.

38:33.532 --> 38:34.532
A schoolteacher?

38:34.533 --> 38:36.033
She wants to meet you.

38:36.034 --> 38:37.034
Now?

38:37.035 --> 38:38.536
It won't take long.

38:38.537 --> 38:40.538
Meet me at the
Hawaiian Village Hotel in half an hour.

38:40.539 --> 38:42.039
Suppose she doesn't
like me?

38:42.040 --> 38:43.541
I never had much luck
with schoolteachers.

38:43.542 --> 38:45.042
She'll like you.

38:45.043 --> 38:46.544
Just don't be late.

38:46.545 --> 38:48.045
I'll pick you up.

38:48.046 --> 38:49.547
Pick <i>who</i> up?

38:49.548 --> 38:52.050
10 minutes, OK?
Good-bye.

38:52.551 --> 38:55.052
I have to run out
for about an hour, Mom.

38:55.053 --> 38:57.133
Oh, but you can't.
Our guests will be arriving soon.

38:57.556 --> 38:59.557
We're having
cocktails at 7:00 and dinner at 8:30.

38:59.558 --> 39:01.559
Who was that
on the telephone?

39:01.560 --> 39:02.560
Maile Duval.

39:02.561 --> 39:04.562
I consented to engage
your beach boys

39:04.563 --> 39:07.064
to provide music
for your party, but I will not...

39:07.065 --> 39:09.567
If you want me back in time, let's
not start anything now, please.

39:09.568 --> 39:11.068
Chadwick?
Yes?

39:11.069 --> 39:12.069
Fix your tie.

39:12.070 --> 39:13.071
Ohh...

39:25.584 --> 39:28.085
She's supposed to meet us
right out here.

39:28.086 --> 39:30.087
Have you met her before?

39:30.088 --> 39:31.589
No, I haven't.

39:31.590 --> 39:32.590
We shouldn't
have any difficulty

39:32.591 --> 39:35.092
in finding
a schoolteacher.

39:35.093 --> 39:38.095
I could spot one
a mile away.

39:38.096 --> 39:39.097
Uh-oh.

39:41.099 --> 39:42.600
Mm-hmm.

39:45.103 --> 39:46.604
Good afternoon.

39:46.605 --> 39:47.605
Good afternoon.

39:47.606 --> 39:49.106
I'm Miss Duval

39:49.107 --> 39:50.608
from the Hawaii
tourist guide service,

39:50.609 --> 39:52.109
and this is Mr. Gates.

39:52.110 --> 39:54.111
How do you do?
I'm Mrs. Ingersol.

39:54.112 --> 39:55.613
And I'm
Abigail Prentace...

39:55.614 --> 39:57.615
How do you do?

39:57.616 --> 39:59.583
The schoolteacher.

39:59.584 --> 40:01.118
Sure...

40:01.119 --> 40:03.621
you can spot them
a mile away.

40:03.622 --> 40:05.122
Won't you join me?

40:05.123 --> 40:06.123
Why, certainly.

40:06.124 --> 40:08.626
We beg your pardon,
ma'am.

40:08.627 --> 40:10.628
I'm terribly sorry.

40:10.629 --> 40:12.630
That's all right,
Miss Duval.

40:12.631 --> 40:14.131
I didn't expect
a tourist guide

40:14.132 --> 40:15.633
dressed
like Mr. Gates.

40:15.634 --> 40:17.134
He <i>is</i> the guide,
isn't he?

40:17.135 --> 40:18.636
Yes, ma'am. These aren't
my working clothes.

40:18.637 --> 40:20.137
My mother's giving
a party tonight.

40:20.138 --> 40:23.140
Mr. Gates comes from one
of our finest families.

40:23.141 --> 40:25.483
Well, that's certainly
in his favor.

40:25.484 --> 40:26.985
I must be
extremely careful

40:26.986 --> 40:28.987
because I'm chaperoning
4 teenage girls.

40:28.988 --> 40:31.489
That's a responsibility
not to be taken lightly.

40:31.490 --> 40:33.491
I get along very well
with teenagers.

40:33.492 --> 40:34.993
I used to be one myself.

40:34.994 --> 40:36.494
And not too long ago.

40:36.495 --> 40:38.497
Frankly, Miss Duval,

40:38.998 --> 40:40.498
I was expecting
an older man.

40:40.499 --> 40:42.500
Miss Prentace,
as part of the service,

40:42.501 --> 40:45.003
I promise to, uh, get a
little older every day.

40:45.004 --> 40:47.505
Of course, if you would
prefer another guide,

40:47.506 --> 40:50.508
I'm sure that the office
could arrange it for you.

40:50.509 --> 40:53.011
We'd like to keep
our customers perfectly satisfied.

40:53.012 --> 40:56.014
Mr. Gates, do you think
you can satisfy

40:56.015 --> 40:58.016
a schoolteacher
and 4 teenage girls?

40:58.017 --> 40:59.517
Oh, I'll sure try,
ma'am.

40:59.518 --> 41:02.020
I-I-I'll do
all I can.

41:02.021 --> 41:03.521
Well, what I mean is,

41:03.522 --> 41:05.523
this is our first trip
to the islands,

41:05.524 --> 41:07.525
and the girls
are naturally curious

41:07.526 --> 41:09.027
about
the local activities,

41:09.028 --> 41:10.528
such as surfboard riding.

41:10.529 --> 41:13.031
Can you arrange
instructions for them?

41:13.032 --> 41:14.032
I'll teach them myself.

41:14.033 --> 41:15.533
You?

41:15.534 --> 41:17.035
I grew up
on a surfboard.

41:17.036 --> 41:19.037
Outriggers, catamarans...
I can handle them all.

41:19.038 --> 41:20.538
How wonderful.

41:20.539 --> 41:23.041
Chad used to be an expert
at all outdoor sports.

41:23.042 --> 41:24.042
Used to be?

41:24.043 --> 41:26.544
Well, before he went
in the army.

41:26.545 --> 41:28.546
He's been gone for 2 years.

41:28.547 --> 41:31.549
He just got back, and I'm
afraid he's a little rusty.

41:31.550 --> 41:34.052
I'm afraid Miss Duval
doesn't realize

41:34.053 --> 41:36.554
how well-oiled
I kept my machinery.

41:36.555 --> 41:40.058
What time do we start
in the morning?

41:40.059 --> 41:41.559
9:00 all right? Here?

41:41.560 --> 41:43.061
We'll be waiting,

41:43.062 --> 41:44.563
and thank you
for coming by.

41:44.847 --> 41:46.564
It's a pleasure
meeting you.

41:46.565 --> 41:48.066
And you.

41:48.067 --> 41:49.068
Thank you.

41:50.569 --> 41:52.070
Maile?

41:59.578 --> 42:01.079
They didn't build
teachers like that when I went to school.

42:01.580 --> 42:05.083
Oh, she's all right,
if you happen to like older women.

42:05.084 --> 42:09.088
If she's older women, the rest of
the group are in big trouble. Ha!

42:10.589 --> 42:12.090
You can drop me off
at my house.

42:12.591 --> 42:14.092
What do you mean
drop you off?

42:14.093 --> 42:15.593
We got to celebrate
my new job.

42:15.594 --> 42:16.595
Aren't you supposed to be
at your mother's party?

42:17.096 --> 42:19.598
Shh. I'm the guide now,
remember?

42:22.134 --> 42:24.102
Oh, do be careful,
daddy.

42:24.103 --> 42:25.603
Those mai-tais can
be mighty powerful.

42:25.604 --> 42:26.604
Yeah!

42:26.605 --> 42:28.106
Oh, thank you,
daddy.

42:28.107 --> 42:29.608
Hello, darlings.

42:30.109 --> 42:31.609
Oh, hello, Mrs. Gates.
This is a lovely party.

42:31.610 --> 42:32.610
Oh, thank you.

42:32.611 --> 42:34.112
I want you to try
some of this dip.

42:34.113 --> 42:35.613
It's an old
Carolina recipe.

42:35.614 --> 42:37.615
My grandmother Polk
brought it all the way

42:37.616 --> 42:39.117
from Charleston
to Savannah.

42:39.118 --> 42:41.119
It's delicious.
Hello, dears.

42:41.120 --> 42:42.120
Good evening.

42:42.121 --> 42:44.623
Oh, isn't it delightful?
It's all so festive.

42:45.124 --> 42:46.624
Oh, Ping Pong,
I want you to be sure

42:46.625 --> 42:48.626
that Mr. karnibad's glass
doesn't get too empty,

42:48.627 --> 42:50.128
<i>s'il vous plait.</i>

42:50.129 --> 42:51.129
<i>Oui, oui,</i>
missy.

42:51.130 --> 42:52.130
Oh, that's French.

42:52.131 --> 42:54.133
Ping Pong's learning
to speak it.

42:54.633 --> 42:56.634
So nice of you
to come to my party.

42:56.635 --> 42:59.637
Oh, there you are,
admiral Anthony.

42:59.638 --> 43:02.140
I see you folks have met
admiral Anthony.

43:02.141 --> 43:03.641
General Anthony,
Mrs. Gates.

43:03.642 --> 43:05.643
Oh, you may be
only a general now,

43:05.644 --> 43:07.145
but it's only
a matter of time

43:07.146 --> 43:09.147
before they make you
an admiral.

43:09.148 --> 43:10.149
Hi, Chad.
Hi, Maile.

43:10.649 --> 43:11.650
Hello, everybody.

43:13.652 --> 43:14.652
Daddy?

43:14.653 --> 43:16.654
Excuse me. Yeah?

43:16.655 --> 43:18.156
Look.

43:18.157 --> 43:19.657
Oh, good. Chad's here.

43:19.658 --> 43:21.659
Yeah, but look
who's with him.

43:21.660 --> 43:23.161
It's that girl.

43:23.162 --> 43:24.162
Yes.

43:24.163 --> 43:25.663
She's very attractive.

43:25.664 --> 43:28.666
Daddy, aren't you
forgetting yourself?

43:28.667 --> 43:31.169
I'm trying, mother.
I'm trying.

43:35.174 --> 43:36.674
Well, hello, Maile.

43:36.675 --> 43:38.176
Nice to see
you again.

43:38.677 --> 43:39.677
Thank you.

43:39.678 --> 43:40.678
Maile,
this is my mother.

43:40.679 --> 43:42.180
It's about time
you two met.

43:42.181 --> 43:43.681
Mom, Maile Duval.

43:43.682 --> 43:45.683
Very glad to meet you,
Mrs. Gates.

43:45.684 --> 43:48.186
Chad's talked
so much about you.

43:48.187 --> 43:49.187
He has?

43:49.188 --> 43:51.189
Oh, that's nice,
Chadwick.

43:51.190 --> 43:53.691
Oh, he's talked
about you, too.

43:53.692 --> 43:56.194
Oh, yes. We've both
talked about you.

43:56.195 --> 43:57.196
Ha ha.

43:57.696 --> 43:58.696
Ahem.

43:58.697 --> 44:00.198
Yes.

44:00.199 --> 44:02.700
Hey, men,
looks like Maile's on the rack.

44:02.701 --> 44:05.203
Are you going to stay
for Chadwick's party, Miss Duval?

44:05.204 --> 44:06.704
I'd like to very much.

44:06.705 --> 44:08.206
