This is very nice
of you.

46:48.367 --> 46:49.868
Good morning,
Miss Prentace.

46:50.035 --> 46:52.870
Well, I must say,
you look more like a guide this morning.

46:52.871 --> 46:54.873
But you still
don't look like a schoolteacher.

46:55.374 --> 46:56.874
Girls, may I present
our guide?

46:56.875 --> 46:59.877
Shall we start
our tour with the pineapple fields?

46:59.878 --> 47:01.379
I hate
pineapples.

47:01.380 --> 47:02.880
Then let's
go there first

47:02.881 --> 47:04.382
and get it
over with.

47:04.383 --> 47:06.384
Are you going with us?

47:06.385 --> 47:08.386
No, thanks.
I have to get back to my office.

47:08.387 --> 47:10.388
Can we give you
a lift?

47:10.389 --> 47:12.391
Oh, that's not necessary.
It's just a few steps.

47:14.393 --> 47:15.894
Thank you.

47:19.898 --> 47:22.400
I hope you don't mind
being this crowded.

47:22.401 --> 47:23.902
I don't mind at all.

47:26.521 --> 47:28.906
Would you mind
closing the door, please?

47:28.907 --> 47:31.409
Well, have fun.

47:31.410 --> 47:32.911
Aloha.

47:50.929 --> 47:52.931
As you know, girls,
this is the island of Oahu,

47:53.432 --> 47:54.432
and Honolulu,
our capital city,

47:54.433 --> 47:55.933
is the largest
of all the islands.

47:55.934 --> 47:57.435
Anybody know
the population?

47:57.436 --> 47:59.937
Population...
Population...

47:59.938 --> 48:02.440
Last count,
500,409.

48:02.441 --> 48:04.942
Correct.
Give the young lady

48:04.943 --> 48:06.944
a 5-pound box
of broken records.

48:06.945 --> 48:08.446
Call me Beverly.

48:08.447 --> 48:09.947
Right, Bev.

48:09.948 --> 48:10.948
I'm Patsy.

48:10.949 --> 48:13.451
My name's Selena,
but call me Sandy.

48:13.452 --> 48:15.453
And what's
your name?

48:15.454 --> 48:17.955
You may call me
Miss Corbett.

48:17.956 --> 48:19.457
La di da da!

48:19.458 --> 48:21.959
You might be
interested to know that since 1778,

48:21.960 --> 48:24.462
we've been welcoming <i>malihinis</i>
from all over the world.

48:24.463 --> 48:25.463
Welcoming what?

48:25.464 --> 48:27.965
